{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":493,"text":"When the Industrial Revolution started,"},{"time":3015,"text":"the amount of carbon sitting\nunderneath Britain in the form of coal"},{"time":7908,"text":"was as big as the amount of carbon\nsitting under Saudi Arabia"},{"time":11107,"text":"in the form of oil."},{"time":13431,"text":"This carbon powered\nthe Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":15990,"text":"it put the \"Great\" in Great Britain,"},{"time":17729,"text":"and led to Britain's temporary\nworld domination."},{"time":22085,"text":"And then, in 1918,\ncoal production in Britain peaked,"},{"time":26530,"text":"and has declined ever since."},{"time":29003,"text":"In due course, Britain started using\noil and gas from the North Sea,"},{"time":33080,"text":"and in the year 2000,"},{"time":35015,"text":"oil and gas production\nfrom the North Sea also peaked,"},{"time":38538,"text":"and they're now on the decline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42136,"text":"These observations about the finiteness"},{"time":44823,"text":"of easily accessible, local,\nsecure fossil fuels,"},{"time":49427,"text":"is a motivation for saying,\n\"Well, what's next?"},{"time":52738,"text":"What is life after fossil fuels\ngoing to be like?"},{"time":55348,"text":"Shouldn't we be thinking hard\nabout how to get off fossil fuels?\""},{"time":58838,"text":"Another motivation,\nof course, is climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62314,"text":"And when people talk\nabout life after fossil fuels"},{"time":64839,"text":"and climate change action,"},{"time":66850,"text":"I think there's a lot of fluff,"},{"time":69304,"text":"a lot of greenwash,\na lot of misleading advertising,"},{"time":72192,"text":"and I feel a duty as a physicist to try\nto guide people around the claptrap"},{"time":76705,"text":"and help people understand the actions\nthat really make a difference,"},{"time":80503,"text":"and to focus on ideas that do add up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85010,"text":"Let me illustrate this"},{"time":86613,"text":"with what physicists call\na back-of-envelope calculation."},{"time":90228,"text":"We love back-of-envelope calculations."},{"time":92097,"text":"You ask a question,\nwrite down some numbers,"},{"time":94192,"text":"and get an answer."},{"time":95379,"text":"It may not be very accurate,\nbut it may make you say, \"Hmm.\""},{"time":98603,"text":"So here's a question:"},{"time":100049,"text":"Imagine if we said, \"Oh yes,\nwe can get off fossil fuels."},{"time":103276,"text":"We'll use biofuels. Problem solved."},{"time":104968,"text":"Transport ... We don't need oil anymore.\""},{"time":107272,"text":"Well, what if we grew\nthe biofuels for a road"},{"time":113730,"text":"on the grass verge\nat the edge of the road?"},{"time":117274,"text":"How wide would the verge\nhave to be for that to work out?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":121511,"text":"OK, so let's put in some numbers."},{"time":123183,"text":"Let's have our cars go\nat 60 miles per hour."},{"time":125917,"text":"Let's say they do 30 miles per gallon."},{"time":127751,"text":"That's the European average for new cars."},{"time":130939,"text":"Let's say the productivity\nof biofuel plantations"},{"time":133287,"text":"is 1,200 liters of biofuel\nper hectare per year."},{"time":136411,"text":"That's true of European biofuels."},{"time":139351,"text":"And let's imagine the cars are spaced\n80 meters apart from each other,"},{"time":142915,"text":"and they're perpetually\ngoing along this road."},{"time":145115,"text":"The length of the road doesn't matter,"},{"time":146979,"text":"because the longer the road,\nthe more biofuel plantation."},{"time":149734,"text":"What do we do with these numbers?"},{"time":151346,"text":"Take the first number, divide by the other\nthree, and get eight kilometers."},{"time":155399,"text":"And that's the answer."},{"time":156579,"text":"That's how wide the plantation\nwould have to be,"},{"time":158963,"text":"given these assumptions."},{"time":161296,"text":"And maybe that makes you say, \"Hmm."},{"time":164053,"text":"Maybe this isn't going\nto be quite so easy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":168230,"text":"And it might make you think,"},{"time":170862,"text":"perhaps there's an issue to do with areas."},{"time":173291,"text":"And in this talk, I'd like to talk\nabout land areas, and ask:"},{"time":177212,"text":"Is there an issue about areas?"},{"time":178719,"text":"The answer is going to be yes,\nbut it depends which country you are in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183403,"text":"So let's start in the United Kingdom,"},{"time":185465,"text":"since that's where we are today."},{"time":187781,"text":"The energy consumption\nof the United Kingdom,"},{"time":190150,"text":"the total energy consumption --\nnot just transport, but everything --"},{"time":194558,"text":"I like to quantify it in lightbulbs."},{"time":196388,"text":"It's as if we've all got\n125 lightbulbs on all the time,"},{"time":199894,"text":"125 kilowatt-hours per day per person"},{"time":203594,"text":"is the energy consumption of the UK."},{"time":206688,"text":"So there's 40 lightbulbs'\nworth for transport,"},{"time":209478,"text":"40 lightbulbs' worth for heating,"},{"time":211154,"text":"and 40 lightbulbs' worth\nfor making electricity,"},{"time":213706,"text":"and other things are relatively small,"},{"time":215644,"text":"compared to those three big fish."},{"time":218301,"text":"It's actually a bigger footprint\nif we take into account"},{"time":221055,"text":"the embodied energy in the stuff\nwe import into our country as well."},{"time":224701,"text":"And 90 percent of this energy, today,\nstill comes from fossil fuels,"},{"time":229459,"text":"and 10 percent, only, from other,\ngreener -- possibly greener -- sources,"},{"time":233161,"text":"like nuclear power and renewables."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236233,"text":"So."},{"time":237542,"text":"That's the UK."},{"time":238823,"text":"The population density of the UK\nis 250 people per square kilometer."},{"time":244068,"text":"I'm now going to show you other countries\nby these same two measures."},{"time":247354,"text":"On the vertical axis, I'm going\nto show you how many lightbulbs --"},{"time":250514,"text":"what our energy consumption per person is."},{"time":252978,"text":"We're at 125 lightbulbs per person,"},{"time":255121,"text":"and that little blue dot there\nis showing you the land area"},{"time":258759,"text":"of the United Kingdom."},{"time":260473,"text":"The population density\nis on the horizontal axis,"},{"time":263286,"text":"and we're 250 people per square kilometer."},{"time":266033,"text":"Let's add European countries in blue,"},{"time":268626,"text":"and you can see there's quite a variety."},{"time":271151,"text":"I should emphasize,\nboth of these axes are logarithmic;"},{"time":274252,"text":"as you go from one gray bar\nto the next gray bar,"},{"time":276831,"text":"you're going up a factor of 10."},{"time":279547,"text":"Next, let's add Asia in red,"},{"time":281912,"text":"the Middle East and North Africa in green,"},{"time":285413,"text":"sub-Saharan Africa in blue,"},{"time":288925,"text":"black is South America,"},{"time":292394,"text":"purple is Central America,"},{"time":294985,"text":"and then in pukey-yellow,\nwe have North America,"},{"time":297812,"text":"Australia and New Zealand."},{"time":300450,"text":"You can see the great diversity\nof population densities"},{"time":303374,"text":"and of per capita consumptions."},{"time":306317,"text":"Countries are different from each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308580,"text":"Top left, we have Canada and Australia,\nwith enormous land areas,"},{"time":312160,"text":"very high per capita consumption --\n200 or 300 lightbulbs per person --"},{"time":316672,"text":"and very low population densities."},{"time":320330,"text":"Top right: Bahrain has\nthe same energy consumption"},{"time":323516,"text":"per person, roughly, as Canada --"},{"time":325523,"text":"over 300 lightbulbs per person,"},{"time":327789,"text":"but their population density\nis a factor of 300 times greater,"},{"time":330835,"text":"1,000 people per square kilometer."},{"time":332688,"text":"Bottom right: Bangladesh has\nthe same population density as Bahrain,"},{"time":337589,"text":"but consumes 100 times less per person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341179,"text":"Bottom left: well, there's no one."},{"time":343686,"text":"But there used to be\na whole load of people."},{"time":345806,"text":"Here's another message from this diagram."},{"time":347783,"text":"I've added on little blue tails\nbehind Sudan, Libya,"},{"time":351173,"text":"China, India, Bangladesh."},{"time":352708,"text":"That's 15 years of progress."},{"time":354867,"text":"Where were they 15 years ago,\nand where are they now?"},{"time":357412,"text":"And the message is,"},{"time":358594,"text":"most countries are going to the right,\nand they're going up."},{"time":361491,"text":"Up and to the right:\nbigger population density"},{"time":363662,"text":"and higher per capita consumption."},{"time":365626,"text":"So, we may be off in the top\nright-hand corner, slightly unusual,"},{"time":369605,"text":"the United Kingdom accompanied by Germany,"},{"time":372016,"text":"Japan, South Korea, the Netherlands,"},{"time":374010,"text":"and a bunch of other\nslightly odd countries,"},{"time":376399,"text":"but many other countries are coming\nup and to the right to join us."},{"time":380728,"text":"So we're a picture, if you like,"},{"time":382795,"text":"of what the future energy consumption"},{"time":384794,"text":"might be looking\nlike in other countries, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388973,"text":"I've also added in this diagram\nnow some pink lines"},{"time":391916,"text":"that go down and to the right."},{"time":393829,"text":"Those are lines of equal\npower consumption per unit area,"},{"time":397694,"text":"which I measure in watts per square meter."},{"time":399789,"text":"So, for example, the middle line there,\n0.1 watts per square meter,"},{"time":403660,"text":"is the energy consumption\nper unit area of Saudi Arabia,"},{"time":407536,"text":"Norway, Mexico in purple,\nand Bangladesh 15 years ago."},{"time":412637,"text":"Half of the world's population\nlives in countries"},{"time":415850,"text":"that are already above that line."},{"time":419710,"text":"The United Kingdom is consuming\n1.25 watts per square meter."},{"time":424926,"text":"So is Germany, and Japan\nis consuming a bit more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429258,"text":"So, let's now say why this is relevant."},{"time":433212,"text":"Why is it relevant?"},{"time":434623,"text":"Well, we can measure\nrenewables in the same units"},{"time":437513,"text":"and other forms of power\nproduction in the same units."},{"time":440728,"text":"Renewables is one of the leading ideas"},{"time":443495,"text":"for how we could get off\nour 90 percent fossil-fuel habit."},{"time":447802,"text":"So here come some renewables."},{"time":449238,"text":"Energy crops deliver\nhalf a watt per square meter"},{"time":451922,"text":"in European climates."},{"time":454709,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":455884,"text":"You might have anticipated that result,"},{"time":457890,"text":"given what I told you about the biofuel\nplantation a moment ago."},{"time":461102,"text":"Well, we consume 1.25 watts\nper square meter."},{"time":464122,"text":"What this means is,"},{"time":465303,"text":"even if you covered the whole\nof the United Kingdom with energy crops,"},{"time":468714,"text":"you couldn't match\ntoday's energy consumption."},{"time":472636,"text":"Wind power produces a bit more --\n2.5 watts per square meter."},{"time":476494,"text":"But that's only twice as big\nas 1.25 watts per square meter."},{"time":481043,"text":"So that means if you wanted, literally,\nto produce total energy consumption"},{"time":485189,"text":"in all forms, on average, from wind farms,"},{"time":487444,"text":"you need wind farms\nhalf the area of the UK."},{"time":491579,"text":"I've got data to back up\nall these assertions, by the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495643,"text":"Next, let's look at solar power."},{"time":498119,"text":"Solar panels, when you put them on a roof,"},{"time":500161,"text":"deliver about 20 watts\nper square meter in England."},{"time":505900,"text":"If you really want to get\na lot from solar panels,"},{"time":508306,"text":"you need to adopt the traditional\nBavarian farming method,"},{"time":511134,"text":"where you leap off the roof,"},{"time":512509,"text":"and coat the countryside\nwith solar panels, too."},{"time":515037,"text":"Solar parks, because of the gaps\nbetween the panels, deliver less."},{"time":518257,"text":"They deliver about 5 watts\nper square meter of land area."},{"time":521688,"text":"And here's a solar park\nin Vermont, with real data,"},{"time":525014,"text":"delivering 4.2 watts per square meter."},{"time":528061,"text":"Remember where we are,\n1.25 watts per square meter,"},{"time":530992,"text":"wind farms 2.5, solar parks about five."},{"time":534897,"text":"So whichever of those renewables you pick,"},{"time":538351,"text":"the message is, whatever mix\nof those renewables you're using,"},{"time":541924,"text":"if you want to power the UK on them,"},{"time":544129,"text":"you're going to need\nto cover something like"},{"time":546254,"text":"20 percent or 25 percent of the country"},{"time":549136,"text":"with those renewables."},{"time":551150,"text":"I'm not saying that's a bad idea;\nwe just need to understand the numbers."},{"time":554686,"text":"I'm absolutely not anti-renewables.\nI love renewables."},{"time":557282,"text":"But I'm also pro-arithmetic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558942,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":560671,"text":"Concentrating solar power in deserts\ndelivers larger powers per unit area,"},{"time":564827,"text":"because you don't have\nthe problem of clouds."},{"time":567202,"text":"So, this facility delivers\n14 watts per square meter;"},{"time":570430,"text":"this one 10 watts per square meter;"},{"time":572165,"text":"and this one in Spain,\n5 watts per square meter."},{"time":574945,"text":"Being generous\nto concentrating solar power,"},{"time":577143,"text":"I think it's perfectly credible it could\ndeliver 20 watts per square meter."},{"time":580831,"text":"So that's nice."},{"time":582021,"text":"Of course, Britain\ndoesn't have any deserts."},{"time":584955,"text":"Yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586135,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":587844,"text":"So here's a summary so far:"},{"time":591035,"text":"All renewables, much\nas I love them, are diffuse."},{"time":593683,"text":"They all have a small power per unit area,"},{"time":595746,"text":"and we have to live with that fact."},{"time":598271,"text":"And that means, if you do want renewables\nto make a substantial difference"},{"time":603587,"text":"for a country like the United Kingdom"},{"time":605399,"text":"on the scale of today's consumption,"},{"time":607515,"text":"you need to be imagining renewable\nfacilities that are country-sized."},{"time":611940,"text":"Not the entire country,"},{"time":613277,"text":"but a fraction of the country,\na substantial fraction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617684,"text":"There are other options\nfor generating power as well,"},{"time":620255,"text":"which don't involve fossil fuels."},{"time":621963,"text":"So there's nuclear power,\nand on this ordinance survey map,"},{"time":625142,"text":"you can see there's a Sizewell B\ninside a blue square kilometer."},{"time":628905,"text":"That's one gigawatt in a square kilometer,"},{"time":630932,"text":"which works out to 1,000 watts\nper square meter."},{"time":633381,"text":"So by this particular metric,"},{"time":635541,"text":"nuclear power isn't\nas intrusive as renewables."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641322,"text":"Of course, other metrics matter, too,"},{"time":643341,"text":"and nuclear power has\nall sorts of popularity problems."},{"time":646964,"text":"But the same goes for renewables as well."},{"time":649025,"text":"Here's a photograph of a consultation\nexercise in full swing"},{"time":651877,"text":"in the little town of Penicuik\njust outside Edinburgh,"},{"time":654589,"text":"and you can see the children\nof Penicuik celebrating"},{"time":657107,"text":"the burning of the effigy of the windmill."},{"time":659501,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":660684,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661758,"text":"People are anti-everything,"},{"time":663111,"text":"and we've got to keep\nall the options on the table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666328,"text":"What can a country like the UK\ndo on the supply side?"},{"time":669991,"text":"Well, the options are,\nI'd say, these three:"},{"time":672934,"text":"power renewables,"},{"time":674136,"text":"and recognizing that they need\nto be close to country-sized;"},{"time":677871,"text":"other people's renewables,"},{"time":679141,"text":"so we could go back and talk very politely"},{"time":681292,"text":"to the people in the top left-hand side\nof the diagram and say,"},{"time":684353,"text":"\"Uh, we don't want\nrenewables in our backyard,"},{"time":686628,"text":"but, um, please could we put\nthem in yours instead?\""},{"time":689246,"text":"And that's a serious option."},{"time":691235,"text":"It's a way for the world\nto handle this issue."},{"time":694843,"text":"So countries like Australia,\nRussia, Libya, Kazakhstan,"},{"time":698999,"text":"could be our best friends\nfor renewable production."},{"time":703356,"text":"And a third option is nuclear power."},{"time":705416,"text":"So that's some supply-side options."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707656,"text":"In addition to the supply levers\nthat we can push --"},{"time":710972,"text":"and remember, we need large amounts,"},{"time":713031,"text":"because at the moment, we get 90 percent\nof our energy from fossil fuels --"},{"time":716582,"text":"in addition to those levers,"},{"time":717966,"text":"we could talk about other ways\nof solving this issue."},{"time":721041,"text":"Namely, we could reduce demand,\nand that means reducing population --"},{"time":724461,"text":"I'm not sure how to do that --"},{"time":726300,"text":"or reducing per capita consumption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729136,"text":"So let's talk about three more big levers"},{"time":731623,"text":"that could really help\non the consumption side."},{"time":733973,"text":"First, transport."},{"time":735151,"text":"Here are the physics principles"},{"time":736718,"text":"that tell you how to reduce\nthe energy consumption of transport."},{"time":739792,"text":"People often say,\n\"Technology can answer everything."},{"time":742262,"text":"We can make vehicles\nthat are 100 times more efficient.\""},{"time":745062,"text":"And that's almost true. Let me show you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747066,"text":"The energy consumption\nof this typical tank here"},{"time":749558,"text":"is 80 kilowatt hours\nper hundred person kilometers."},{"time":753006,"text":"That's the average European car."},{"time":757347,"text":"Eighty kilowatt hours."},{"time":758522,"text":"Can we make something 100 times better"},{"time":760634,"text":"by applying the physics\nprinciples I just listed?"},{"time":762971,"text":"Yes. Here it is. It's the bicycle."},{"time":764638,"text":"It's 80 times better\nin energy consumption,"},{"time":767308,"text":"and it's powered by biofuel, by Weetabix."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769556,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":771718,"text":"And there are other options in between,"},{"time":773609,"text":"because maybe the lady\nin the tank would say,"},{"time":775760,"text":"\"No, that's a lifestyle change.\nDon't change my lifestyle, please.\""},{"time":778940,"text":"We could persuade her to take a train,\nstill a lot more efficient than a car,"},{"time":782611,"text":"but that might be a lifestyle change."},{"time":784410,"text":"Or there's the EcoCAR, top-left."},{"time":786018,"text":"It comfortably accommodates one teenager\nand it's shorter than a traffic cone,"},{"time":789777,"text":"and it's almost as efficient as a bicycle,"},{"time":791837,"text":"as long as you drive it\nat 15 miles per hour."},{"time":795299,"text":"In between, perhaps\nsome more realistic options"},{"time":797550,"text":"on the transport lever\nare electric vehicles,"},{"time":800539,"text":"so electric bikes\nand electric cars in the middle,"},{"time":802942,"text":"perhaps four times as energy efficient\nas the standard petrol-powered tank."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808778,"text":"Next, there's the heating lever."},{"time":810700,"text":"Heating is a third of our energy\nconsumption in Britain,"},{"time":814215,"text":"and quite a lot of that\nis going into homes"},{"time":816312,"text":"and other buildings,"},{"time":817719,"text":"doing space heating and water heating."},{"time":819720,"text":"So here's a typical crappy British house."},{"time":822028,"text":"It's my house, with a Ferrari out front."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824771,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":825860,"text":"What can we do to it?"},{"time":827037,"text":"Well, the laws of physics\nare written up there,"},{"time":830722,"text":"which describe how the power\nconsumption for heating"},{"time":835994,"text":"is driven by the things you can control."},{"time":837926,"text":"The things you can control\nare the temperature difference"},{"time":840844,"text":"between the inside and the outside."},{"time":842551,"text":"There's this remarkable technology\ncalled a thermostat:"},{"time":845189,"text":"you grasp it, rotate it to the left,"},{"time":846949,"text":"and your energy consumption\nin the home will decrease."},{"time":849502,"text":"I've tried it. It works.\nSome people call it a lifestyle change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852629,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":853737,"text":"You can also get the fluff men\nin to reduce the leakiness"},{"time":857241,"text":"of your building -- put fluff\nin the walls, fluff in the roof,"},{"time":860234,"text":"a new front door, and so forth."},{"time":863452,"text":"The sad truth is,\nthis will save you money."},{"time":866061,"text":"That's not sad, that's good."},{"time":867425,"text":"But the sad truth is,"},{"time":868627,"text":"it'll only get about 25 percent\nof the leakiness of your building"},{"time":871850,"text":"if you do these things,\nwhich are good ideas."},{"time":874569,"text":"If you really want to get a bit closer\nto Swedish building standards"},{"time":877852,"text":"with a crappy house like this,"},{"time":879526,"text":"you need to be putting\nexternal insulation on the building,"},{"time":882996,"text":"as shown by this block of flats in London."},{"time":886652,"text":"You can also deliver heat\nmore efficiently using heat pumps,"},{"time":889681,"text":"which use a smaller bit\nof high-grade energy like electricity"},{"time":893175,"text":"to move heat from your garden\ninto your house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896676,"text":"The third demand-side option\nI want to talk about,"},{"time":899070,"text":"the third way to reduce energy\nconsumption is: read your meters."},{"time":902240,"text":"People talk a lot about smart meters,"},{"time":904093,"text":"but you can do it yourself."},{"time":905464,"text":"Use your own eyes and be smart."},{"time":907413,"text":"Read your meter, and if you're anything\nlike me, it'll change your life."},{"time":911100,"text":"Here's a graph I made."},{"time":912556,"text":"I was writing a book\nabout sustainable energy,"},{"time":914724,"text":"and a friend asked me,"},{"time":915902,"text":"\"How much energy do you use at home?\""},{"time":917740,"text":"I was embarrassed; I didn't actually know."},{"time":919784,"text":"And so I started reading\nthe meter every week."},{"time":922009,"text":"The old meter readings are shown\nin the top half of the graph,"},{"time":925825,"text":"and then 2007 is shown\nin green at the bottom."},{"time":928074,"text":"That was when I was reading\nthe meter every week."},{"time":930420,"text":"And my life changed,"},{"time":931610,"text":"because I started doing experiments\nand seeing what made a difference."},{"time":934989,"text":"My gas consumption plummeted,"},{"time":936418,"text":"because I started tinkering\nwith the thermostat"},{"time":938661,"text":"and the timing on the heating system,"},{"time":940484,"text":"and I knocked more than half\noff my gas bills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942721,"text":"There's a similar story\nfor my electricity consumption,"},{"time":945628,"text":"where switching off the DVD\nplayers, the stereos,"},{"time":949214,"text":"the computer peripherals\nthat were on all the time,"},{"time":952032,"text":"and just switching them on\nwhen I needed them,"},{"time":954251,"text":"knocked another third\noff my electricity bills, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958142,"text":"So we need a plan that adds up."},{"time":959932,"text":"I've described for you six big levers."},{"time":962546,"text":"We need big action,"},{"time":963736,"text":"because we get 90 percent\nof our energy from fossil fuels,"},{"time":966522,"text":"and so you need to push hard\non most, if not all, of these levers."},{"time":971288,"text":"Most of these levers\nhave popularity problems,"},{"time":973598,"text":"and if there is a lever\nyou don't like the use of,"},{"time":977288,"text":"well, please do bear in mind\nthat means you need even stronger effort"},{"time":981129,"text":"on the other levers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983456,"text":"So I'm a strong advocate\nof having grown-up conversations"},{"time":986631,"text":"that are based on numbers and facts."},{"time":988916,"text":"And I want to close with this map\nthat just visualizes for you"},{"time":992716,"text":"the requirement of land and so forth"},{"time":996277,"text":"in order to get just\n16 lightbulbs per person"},{"time":999365,"text":"from four of the big possible sources."},{"time":1002474,"text":"So, if you wanted to get 16 lightbulbs --"},{"time":1005658,"text":"remember, today our total energy\nconsumption is 125 lightbulbs' worth --"},{"time":1010003,"text":"if you wanted 16 from wind,"},{"time":1012250,"text":"this map visualizes a solution for the UK."},{"time":1015101,"text":"It's got 160 wind farms,\neach 100 square kilometers in size,"},{"time":1019282,"text":"and that would be a twentyfold increase\nover today's amount of wind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023190,"text":"Nuclear power:\nto get 16 lightbulbs per person,"},{"time":1026122,"text":"you'd need two gigawatts\nat each of the purple dots on the map."},{"time":1029235,"text":"That's a fourfold increase\nover today's levels of nuclear power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034069,"text":"Biomass: to get 16 lightbulbs per person,"},{"time":1036791,"text":"you'd need a land area something\nlike three and a half Wales' worth,"},{"time":1041823,"text":"either in our country,\nor in someone else's country,"},{"time":1044429,"text":"possibly Ireland, possibly somewhere else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046496,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047599,"text":"And a fourth supply-side option:"},{"time":1049414,"text":"concentrating solar power\nin other people's deserts."},{"time":1052554,"text":"If you wanted to get 16 lightbulbs' worth,"},{"time":1055017,"text":"then we're talking\nabout these eight hexagons"},{"time":1058056,"text":"down at the bottom right."},{"time":1059391,"text":"The total area of those hexagons\nis two Greater London's worth"},{"time":1063640,"text":"of someone else's Sahara,"},{"time":1065753,"text":"and you'll need power lines\nall the way across Spain and France"},{"time":1068784,"text":"to bring the power\nfrom the Sahara to Surrey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072595,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073769,"text":"We need a plan that adds up."},{"time":1076295,"text":"We need to stop shouting\nand start talking."},{"time":1080209,"text":"And if we can have\na grown-up conversation,"},{"time":1084456,"text":"make a plan that adds up and get building,"},{"time":1086941,"text":"maybe this low-carbon revolution\nwill actually be fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1089969,"text":"Thank you very much for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091731,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}